Please answer my code questions using the given API following this format: <<<api>>>: $API
<<<code>>>: $CODE
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION.
Question: How to append text to an existing file in Java?: :I need to append text repeatedly to an existing file in Java. How do I do that?
Please using this api: PrintWriter.write.
Answer: <<<api>>>: PrintWriter.write
<<<code>>>: PrintWriter pw = new PrintWriter(new FileWriter("file.txt", true));
pw.println("text to append");
pw.close();
<<<explanation>>>: This code will append the text "text to append" to the end of the file "file.txt". The true parameter in the FileWriter constructor tells the FileWriter to append to the file, rather than overwriting it.
Question: How to read a file in Java?: :I need to read a file in Java. How do I do that?
Please using this api: BufferedReader.readLine.
Answer: <<<api>>>: BufferedReader.readLine
<<<code>>>: BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file.txt"));
String line;
while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}
br.close();
<<<explanation>>>: This code will read the file "file.txt" line by line and print each line to the console. The BufferedReader.readLine method returns null when there are no more lines to read.
Question: How to write a file in Java?: :I need to write a file in Java. How do I do that?
Please using this api: PrintWriter.write.
Answer: <<<api>>>: PrintWriter.write
<<<code>>>: PrintWriter pw = new PrintWriter(new FileWriter("file.txt"));
pw.println("text to write");
pw.close();
<<<explanation>>>: This code will write the text "text to write" to the file "file.txt". The PrintWriter.println method writes a line of text to the file, and the PrintWriter.close method closes the file.
